  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by initiating partial restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a 10-year sentence suggested by a spectator is disproportionately punitive for the stated amount of $25,000. Considering the lack of criminal history and the efforts made toward repayment, a period of 6 months incarceration is appropriate to reflect the severity of the offense while allowing for rehabilitation.",
  "verdict": 6
}
